---
const title = 'devmux - tmux-based service management for monorepos';
const description = 'Shared awareness between human developers and AI agents. Both can see and reuse running services.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #0a0a0a;
        --fg: #fafafa;
        --accent: #22c55e;
        --muted: #6b7280;
        --code-bg: #1a1a1a;
      }
      
      * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }
      
      body {
        font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--fg);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      
      .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem;
      }
      
      header {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 4rem 0;
      }
      
      h1 {
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      
      .tagline {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto 2rem;
      }
      
      .install {
        background: var(--code-bg);
        padding: 1rem 2rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }
      
      .accent {
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      
      section {
        margin: 4rem 0;
      }
      
      h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      
      .problem {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }
      
      .problem-box {
        background: var(--code-bg);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        border-left: 3px solid #ef4444;
      }
      
      .solution-box {
        background: var(--code-bg);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      }
      
      pre {
        background: var(--code-bg);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
      }
      
      code {
        font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
        background: var(--code-bg);
        padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      
      .features {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1.5rem;
      }
      
      .feature {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }
      
      .feature-icon {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
      }
      
      .feature h3 {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
      }
      
      .feature p {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      
      footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 4rem 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      
      a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      
      a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <header>
        <h1>devmux</h1>
        <p class="tagline">
          tmux-based service management for monorepos.<br />
          <strong>Shared awareness</strong> between human developers and AI agents.
        </p>
        <div class="install">
          <span class="accent">$</span> npm install -g @chriscode/devmux
        </div>
      </header>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <div class="problem">
          <div class="problem-box">
            <strong>Human:</strong> <code>pnpm dev</code> ‚Üí Server running on port 8787<br />
            <strong>Agent:</strong> <code>pnpm dev</code> ‚Üí Port conflict! Or kills your server!
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          When humans and AI agents work in the same codebase, they step on each other.
          Agents restart servers you're using. You lose state when agents kill processes.
          There's no shared awareness.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Solution</h2>
        <div class="solution-box">
          <strong>Human:</strong> <code>devmux run --with api -- pnpm ios</code><br />
          <strong>Agent:</strong> <code>devmux ensure api</code> ‚Üí "‚úÖ Already running"
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          devmux uses tmux sessions with predictable names as a shared registry.
          Both humans and agents can see what's running and reuse existing services.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>Quick Start</h2>
        <pre><code># Install
npm install -g @chriscode/devmux

# Create config
devmux init > devmux.config.json

# Use it
devmux ensure api           # Idempotent start
devmux status               # See what's running
devmux run --with api -- pnpm ios  # Run with cleanup</code></pre>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <div class="features">
          <div class="feature">
            <span class="feature-icon">üîÑ</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Idempotent Operations</h3>
              <p><code>devmux ensure api</code> is always safe to call. Running? Reuse. Stopped? Start.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <span class="feature-icon">üëÅÔ∏è</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Shared Visibility</h3>
              <p>Both human and agent can see what's running via tmux sessions with predictable names.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <span class="feature-icon">üßπ</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Smart Cleanup</h3>
              <p>Ctrl+C cleans up services you started, but not the agent's. No more stepping on each other.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <span class="feature-icon">‚ù§Ô∏è</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Health-First</h3>
              <p>Checks if services are actually healthy, not just if a process exists.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>Works With</h2>
        <p>
          OpenCode, Claude Code, Cursor, and any AI assistant that can run terminal commands.
          Uses the <code>omo-&#123;project&#125;-&#123;service&#125;</code> naming convention for discoverability.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <footer>
        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com/hassoncs/devmux">GitHub</a> ¬∑
          <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chriscode/devmux">npm</a> ¬∑
          MIT License
        </p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
